DBEM - DataBase tools for Electron Microscopy


-------------
Requirements:
-------------
- Web server Apache
- MySQL (4.0 or higher)
- PHP4 (4.0.4 or higher) with MySQL 
- JavaScript-enabled browser
- CSS-enabled browser


----------
Unpacking:
----------

Unpack the archive into your web server directory:
	$ cd /yourwwwdir
	$ tar zxvf dbem[version].tgz

--------------
Configuration:
--------------
	$ cd dbem

	- edit the file config.php
	- set your MySQL parameters:

	$DB_HOST	= "[SQL HOST]";
	$DB_USER	= "[SQL USER]";
	$DB_PASSWORD	= "[SQL PASS]";
	$DB		= "[database]";

----------------------------
Add mrc.so in php.ini:
----------------------------

	$ vi /etc/php.ini and locate the extension directory and add
				mrc.so under [Extension section]:

	; Directory in which the loadable extensions (modules) reside.
	extension_dir = "./"
	extension_dir = /usr/lib/php/extensions

	[extension section]
	extension=mrc.so

	Copy the extension file, and restart the web server

	$ cp ext/mrc.so /usr/lib/php/extensions/
	$ /etc/init.d/apache[version] restart

--------------
run:
--------------
	Go to http://yourhost/dbem/

